<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-01-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-01-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="376" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d376">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wetter</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Strobel</persName></hi>.</head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tamatave</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-01-27"><hi rend="italic">January 27,
                                        1894</hi></date>.</dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 7.]</seg></opener>
                            <p>I regret to say that the report here is prevalent that Mr. Waller
                                absconded.” This I will state: I find he has appointed himself
                                administrator of Crockett’s estate and taken over the entire assets
                                of said estate and carried them with him. As soon as I can I will
                                report in a separate dispatch on this subject.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>